  "body": "I think that I have found a bug, @djrtwo confirmed it on gitter.\r\n\r\nThe current slashing conditions are fine for normal finalizations without slots between potential justifiable/finalize-able blocks (i.e epoch_boundary blocks) or if shuffling is deterministic within the context of a finalized block.\r\nBut, in the current spec, neither of these two conditions are met. We allow attestation between epoch_boundary blocks and a reshuffling is possible.\r\n\r\nI tried to describe it more detailed here:\r\nhttps://docs.google.com/presentation/d/10gODMelMaeZzKgRuBk1G0At-wwC5VcCkvBoMhkHQU80/edit?usp=sharing\r\n\r\n----------------------------------------\r\nAs a solution, I would propose to change the current is_double_vote to something like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\ndef is_double_vote(attestation_data_1: AttestationData,\r\n                   attestation_data_2: AttestationData) -> bool\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Assumes ``attestation_data_1`` is distinct from ``attestation_data_2`` \r\n    Returns True if the provided ``AttestationData`` are slashable\r\n    due to a 'double vote'.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    return attestation_data_1.epoch_boundary_root != attestation_data_2.epoch_boundary_root AND  attestation_data_1.slot // EPOCH_LENGTH == attestation_data_2.slot // EPOCH_LENGTH\r\n```\r\n",
