    "body": "Second thought, let's have the fix like this:\r\n\r\n```Python\r\ndef is_double_vote(attestation_data_1: AttestationData,\r\n                   attestation_data_2: AttestationData) -> bool\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Assumes ``attestation_data_1`` is distinct from ``attestation_data_2`` \r\n    Returns True if the provided ``AttestationData`` are slashable\r\n    due to a 'double vote'.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    return height(attestation_data_1.epoch_boundary_root) == height(attestation_data_2.epoch_boundary_root)\r\n```\r\n(This covers the case where validators want to attest to an epoch_boundary_block from an older epoch than the current epoch)",
